# NestAid Cursor Rules

## Font Families

### Titles/Headings
- All titles, headings (h1, h2, h3, etc.), and heading-level text should use:
  - font-family: 'Playfair Display', 'Playfair Display Fallback';
  - Import from: `next/font/google` using `Playfair_Display`
  - Apply using: `${playfair.className}` or inline style

### Paragraphs/Body Text
- All paragraphs, body text, and non-heading text should use:
  - font-family: 'Inter', 'Inter Fallback';
  - Import from: `next/font/google` using `Inter`
  - Apply using: `${inter.className}` or inline style

## Code Style Guidelines

### Typography Usage
```typescript
// For headings/titles
<h1 className={`${playfair.className} ...`}>Title Text</h1>

// For paragraphs/body text
<p className={`${inter.className} ...`}>Paragraph text</p>
```

### Font Imports
Always import fonts at the top of component files:
```typescript
import { Playfair_Display, Inter } from "next/font/google"

const playfair = Playfair_Display({
  weight: ["400", "500", "600", "700"],
  subsets: ["latin"]
})

const inter = Inter({
  weight: ["400", "500", "600", "700"],
  subsets: ["latin"]
})
```

## Best Practices
- Use Playfair Display for all heading elements (h1-h6)
- Use Inter for all body text, paragraphs, links, and general content
- Maintain consistency across all pages and components
- Avoid using system fonts or other font families unless specifically required





